**who —** LICHEN — a life-science sphere — the brainless mind

**what —** Not a plant, not a single thing — a lichen is a fungus and an alga (and often more) so fully merged that they look and act like one organism, with a name, a shape, and a life of their own. A self made of partners, able to live where neither could alone, even surviving the vacuum of space. Identity as a collaboration.

**where —** intelligence without a brain  Framework inputs: the living; the rule; the signal; the open question  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)

**why —** Not a plant, not a single thing — a lichen is a fungus and an alga (and often more) so fully merged that they look and act like one organism, with a name, a shape, and a life of their own. A self made of partners, able to live where neither could alone, even surviving the vacuum of space. Identity as a collaboration.

**how —** Crystallized from the public record of the science.

**◌ the mythos —** Not a plant, not a single thing — a lichen is a fungus and an alga (and often more) so fully merged that they look and act like one organism, with a name, a shape, and a life of their own. A self made of partners, able to live where neither could alone, even surviving the vacuum of space. Identity as a collaboration. where a mind appears with no neurons in it

